---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Privacy" description="Voice Inbox privacy and data handling information.">
  <style>
    .content {
      max-width: 860px;
    }
    .content section {
      margin-top: 38px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding-bottom: 26px;
    }
    .content section:last-child {
      border-bottom: 0;
    }
  </style>

  <article class="content">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy</p>
    <h1>Local-first by design.</h1>
    <p>
      This page explains how Voice Inbox handles audio, documents, and network access in user-facing terms.
      It is not a substitute for legal review before app store publication.
    </p>

    <section>
      <h2>Audio recognition</h2>
      <p>
        Voice Inbox runs speech recognition locally on the Android device after the speech model is installed.
        Audio files are read from the folder selected by the user.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Network access</h2>
      <p>
        Network access is needed for the first speech model download. The app should not be described as never using network access.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Selected files and folders</h2>
      <p>
        The app uses Android document access selected by the user: one output <code>.txt</code> or <code>.md</code> document and one audio folder.
        It appends recognized text only to the selected output document.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Catalog storage</h2>
      <p>
        Voice Inbox keeps a private local catalog of discovered audio files and processing state so it can distinguish New and Processed files.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>External providers and Android services</h2>
      <p>
        Android document providers, media decoders, storage behavior, and background scheduling are provided by the operating system or selected providers.
        Voice Inbox cannot control or make privacy claims on behalf of those external components.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
